50|$|Employers {{are subject}} to {{unemployment}} taxes by the federal and all state governments. The tax is a percentage of taxable wages with a cap. The tax rate and cap vary by jurisdiction and by employer's industry and experience rating. For 2009, the typical maximum tax per employee was under $1,000. Some states also impose <b>unemployment,</b> disability <b>insurance,</b> or similar taxes on employees.|$|R
