25|$|Because the {{government}} {{had to rely on}} the support of the Liberals it was unable to pass any radical legislation. The most significant achievement was the Wheatley Housing Act, which began a building programme of 500,000 homes for rental to low paid workers. Legislation on education, <b>unemployment,</b> social <b>insurance</b> and tenant protection was also passed. Although no major changes were introduced, the main achievement of {{the government}} was to demonstrate that Labour were capable of governing.|$|R
40|$|ENACTMENT OF TAX MEASURES BY LEGISLATURE - INITIATIVE CONSTITUTIONAL AMENDMENT. Amends the Constitution to require, {{notwithstanding}} any contrary {{provision of}} the Constitution, a vote of two-thirds of the membership of each house of the Legislature to impose any tax or to change the rate, base or other aspects of any tax. Such votes must be by roll call entered in the journal. Contributions to <b>Unemployment</b> Compensation <b>Insurance,</b> including disability coverage, would be exempted from the requirement. Fiscal impact: none...|$|R
